This is a simple walkthrough on how to use git.
- A folder is created on desktop and open via git bash
- the folder is initialized using the "git init" command 
- files are then created inside the folder by running the command "touch file-name"
- Use visual code studio or any other editor and open the folder
- include contents in the files 
- add all files to staging area via this command "git add . "
- commit the changes by " git commit -m 'Initial commit'